======================================================================
2D Joint (ϖ + i) Clustering Analysis — ETNO Sample
======================================================================
  N = 19

--- 2D Spherical Rayleigh Test ---
  Mean resultant (Rx, Ry, Rz) = (0.3432, 0.3301, 0.2983)
  R_sphere = 0.5619
  Test statistic (3NR²) = 18.00
  p-value (χ²(3)) = 0.000440

--- Monte Carlo Null 1 (randomize ϖ, fix i) ---
  p-value = 0.0066  (N_MC = 50000)
  Null median R = 0.3491
  Null 95% CI  = [0.3003, 0.5074]

--- Monte Carlo Null 2 (randomize ϖ + i, full spherical uniform) ---
  p-value = 0.0001  (N_MC = 50000)
  Null median R = 0.2056
  Null 95% CI  = [0.0625, 0.3976]

--- 1D Kuiper Test on ϖ (for comparison) ---
  Kuiper statistic = 0.4365
  Monte Carlo p    = 0.0103

--- 1D Kuiper Test on sin(i) ---
  Kuiper statistic = 0.7378
  Monte Carlo p    = 0.0000

======================================================================
KEY FINDING
======================================================================
  2D joint p (ϖ random, i fixed):  p = 0.0066
  2D joint p (both random):         p = 0.0001
  1D Rayleigh p (ϖ only):           p = 0.008 (uncorrected)
  The 2D analysis preserves the clustering signal but at reduced
  power — consistent with the paper's claim that 1D statistics
  are incomplete but 2D tests at N=19 lack statistical power.
